# Expo Router Conventions

This project uses **expo-router v6** with file-based routing.

## File Naming & Structure

- Route files: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g. `add-friend.tsx`, `edit-profile.tsx`)
- Route groups: `(group-name)/` — `(auth)`, `(tabs)`, `(modals)` — do NOT appear in URL
- Dynamic routes: `[id].tsx` (e.g. `app/post/[id].tsx`)
- Layouts: `_layout.tsx` per folder

## Navigation

```tsx
import { router, useLocalSearchParams } from 'expo-router';

router.push('/profile/123');
router.push({ pathname: '/post/[id]', params: { id: postId } });
router.back();

const { id } = useLocalSearchParams<{ id: string }>();
```

- Use typed `useLocalSearchParams<{ id: string }>()` — never `any`
- Use `<Link href="..." />` for static navigation, `router.push` inside handlers
- Register new routes in the appropriate `_layout.tsx` `<Stack.Screen name="..." />` if they need custom presentation

## Screen Template

```tsx
import { View } from 'react-native';
import { ScreenHeader, Text } from '@/components/ui';

export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <View className="flex-1 bg-background-light dark:bg-background-dark">
      <ScreenHeader title="My Screen" />
      {/* content */}
    </View>
  );
}
```

## Modals

Modal screens live under `app/(modals)/` and are configured in `app/(modals)/_layout.tsx` (current default: `presentation: 'transparentModal'`, `animation: 'fade'`).

```tsx
// Open a modal
router.push('/(modals)/incoming-call');

// Dismiss
router.back();
```

Rules:
- Any new modal route → put the file in `app/(modals)/` and add `<Stack.Screen name="..." />` to `app/(modals)/_layout.tsx`
- For one-off modals at the root stack (e.g. `create-post`, see `app/_layout.tsx`), register them with `options={{ presentation: 'modal' }}`
- DO NOT use `router.replace` to dismiss a modal — it breaks the back stack; use `router.back()`
- DO NOT navigate to a modal with `<Link>` if you need imperative control after dismiss — use `router.push` so you can read the result via context/state

## Don'ts

- DO NOT import `NavigationContainer` — expo-router owns it
- DO NOT use `react-navigation/native-stack` directly — use `Stack` from `expo-router`
- DO NOT create deeply nested folders for screens that don't need them
- DO NOT skip `SafeAreaView` / safe-area handling on screens with header
